         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" resp="cmr"><head>Translation</head>
            <p>With good fortune, for Hesychios the founder </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>On this acclamation, see Reall. f. Ant. u. Christ. I., col. 229, s.v. feliciter.</p>
            <p>Presumably to be associated with the Hesychii of <ref type="inscription">C07100</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C07300</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C59400</ref>,
               <ref type="inscription">C69000</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C69700</ref>, q.v.,
               and the lettering as drawn shows no features that conflict with a date in the fourth or early fifth century:
               see <ref type="inscription">C69000</ref>.  If that is correct, the inscription, if not a stray from the house of Hesychios (on which see <ref type="inscription">C69000</ref>), must indicate that Hesychios constructed some other building in the neighbourhood.</p>
         </div>
         
